
/ Polyprotic Acids
story 14_5
  >
    We can classify acids by the number of protons per molecule that they can give up in a reaction. Acids such as HCl, HNO<sub>3</sub>, and HCN that contain one ionizable hydrogen atom in each molecule are called  **monoprotic acids**. Their reactions with water are:
    
